-- pd.package: roboto-typography package
name: fastn-community.github.io/roboto-typography

This FTD font `roboto-typography` can be used for your ftd web projects. 

You can use this roboto-typography inside the `FTD` project. Follow below
instructions to use this font package.

-- ds.h3: How to use roboto-typography?

To use this roboto-typography inside your `ftd` web project, if you are
using our [doc-site](https://github.com/fifthtry/doc-site) theme then you just
have to pass types to `ds.page`

Let's say you are using `doc-site` inside your project then, it's as simple as
making a sandwich.

-- ds.code: Add this to your FASTN.ftd
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: fastn-community.github.io/roboto-typography

-- ds.markdown:

Now import `roboto-typography` inside `.ftd` file as shown below:

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- import: fastn-community.github.io/roboto-typography


-- ds.markdown: 

add `roboto-typography` `types` to `ds.page` `types` attribute as shown
below:

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- ds.page:
types: $roboto-typography.types

-- ds.markdown: 

Once you add `types: $roboto-typography.types` inside your `.ftd` file,
`roboto-typography` will be added as `fastn` default typography to your
`ds.page` and to all components you add inside `ds.page`.

If you're not using `doc-site` theme and building your own `fastn` web theme.
Then, add `roboto-typography` dependency into `FASTN.ftd` file.

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: fastn-community.github.io/roboto-typography

-- ds.markdown:

Once you add above dependency, then import `roboto-typography` inside your
`.ftd` file:

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- import: fastn-community.github.io/roboto-typography

-- ds.markdown:

Done! `roboto-typography` is now added. Lets define a `page` component:

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd
download: my-ds.ftd

\-- import: fastn-community.github.io/roboto-typography

\-- component page:
caption title:
body body:
children wrap:
ftd.type-data types: $roboto-typography.types

\-- ftd.column:
width: fill-container
spacing.fixed.px: 32
padding.px: 30
background.solid: $inherited.colors.background.base
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border-strong
border-radius.px: 10
margin-vertical.px: 10

\-- ftd.text: $page.title
role: $inherited.types.heading-large
color: $inherited.colors.text-strong

\-- ftd.text: 
role: $inherited.types.copy-regular
color: $inherited.colors.text

$page.body

\-- ftd.column:
width: fill-container
children: $page.wrap

\-- end: ftd.column

\-- end: ftd.column

\-- end: page


-- ds.markdown:

In above code snippet we defined `page` component which has `types`, `title`,
`body` and  `wrap` attributes.

The `types` attribute used to pass a typography to it. In above example we have
added `$roboto-typography.types` as default `ftd.type-data`. The
`ftd.type-data` contains all `fastn` default `inherited` types.

The `title` attribute will be used for adding `page` titles. 

The `body` attribute is used to add body to `page` component, the `body` can
contain multiple pagragraphs, lists and any markdown format content.

The `wrap` attribute allows adding child components to `page` component. You can
add any other component inside `page`.

Click on download icon on above code snippet `my-ds.ftd` file will be
downloaded. 

-- ds.rendered:
download: types.ftd

-- ds.rendered.input:

\-- import: <your-fastn-package-name>/my-ds

\-- my-ds.page: I am a page title

I am `page` component body. Body can contain multiple paragraphs, links etc.

